Incredible amount of game for the price. All the gameplay fundamentals are 
super solid. Only sore point is the user interface is lacking some key 
functionality. For instance: turn skipping (set mvt to 0) for individual 
units; being able to just see units with no current orders; saving 
list-filter preferences between instances of loading the unit list; the end 
turn button changing color or something when there's no key outstanding 
actions to be taken; some sort of guard/sentry mode; a heal/refuel mode; an 
"upgrade all" button... It just makes certain routine actions unnecessarily 
tedious. Add that ui functionality and I'd give it 6 stars =) One idea to 
do this without adding bulk/clutter to the ui for everyone would be to have 
a more extensive options menu where you can tweak this stuff.

Though thats just my opinion or course. Also, I wish there would be some kind of battleships, maybe as a late game fighting vessle since they would be extremely powerful but cost a lot in terms of upkeep and initial industry cost. It would be great if these two things were fixed/added but of course this is just my opinion, nonetheless this is still an aamzing game which has done a lot of things right compared to other 4x games

I'd like to see more detail and ways of intervening on planet quality, but otherwise this is an excellent purchase.

UPDATE: Years of gameplay and my love for this title has yet to diminish. Made it onto my list of All-Timers. This is so good that I bought the premium version after playing the demo for ten minutes. The outstanding attention to gameplay should be the benchmark for all RPG/Strategy games. Great job, well worth the money.

Controls- Great UI! The only "small" complaint I have is the size of some of the buttons. Nothing serious but it does result in having to tap in the same area a few times to get the desired effect. Small complaint. If I could remove only half a star from the controls rating I would.  Gameplay- Excellent world builder with deep political nuances and strategies. This game will have you feeling like the overlord of a small (or large depending on your game) galaxy. Don't go into this game expecting boardgame level, turn based strategy. The game is more centered around discovery, politics, resource management and world building.  Graphics- They're good. If I understand correctly, all of the graphics are done by one of the Trese brothers and it kinda shows. Not that they're bad, but they do have a certain "recycled" feel to them. That aside, I love the "Firefly" aesthetic to all of the art in the game.  Overall- Great game that meshes together excellently. Would recommend to anyone looking to get a deep, self-paced gaming experience on an android device.

This game is awesome. If you like deep civ building strategy, then this is the game for you. The faction interactions are a little simplistic in my opinion, and the relatively minimalistic combat sometimes leaves the game feeling like it lacks focus on a specific element. However, resource management is where this game shines. Expanding colonies, supporting old worlds, and funding a war effort all take precise planning, and a few minor errors could send your empire spiraling to bankruptcy. Its challenging, but success is extremely rewarding. It has a bit of a high learning curve, but its worth it.

Very impressive space-based 4X strategy game. Like all of Trese Brothers games, this one is continually upgraded based on user feedback and gameplay feedback.  Take control of a splinter group of explorers as they survive a catastrophe/migration event and find them selves needing to explore/expand a new home of star systems.  Aliens are less keen to accomodate their new neighbors, and prepare to attack while you settle, explore, research tech/weapons, and hopefully keep them at bay until you are strong enough to eliminate the alien threat(s).  Multiple maps, multiple difficulty settings, a heart research tree are at the heart of this game.  In addition to this dilemma, add in intra-colony political unrest (they really don't like each other), and you have quite the challenge that can be played on PC (Steam), tablet/phone wherever you are.  Pickup and play whenever you have a few moments to set directives, research, battle, build resources, move fleets, invade planets, etc... An amazing value! A demo version (limited maps, etc...) is available, why don't you try it!? Upgrade to the full version for only a couple bucks.  Full support through their forums, friendly advice too!

If you like turn based strategy games, then this is for you, very good game, love the ability to play a gane like this on my phone
Kind of like a sid miers civilization in space and like all their other games the updates keep coming great job again bros

The Trese Brothers have yet to disappoint.  They build and continue to craft games that are smart and tough and keep me interested for a long time.  Works great on Galaxy S5.  Can put it down at a moment's notice and not lose a bunch of progress.  They are continually improving ALL of their games, taking feedback from players, improving the experience and adding new stuff.  The best strategic turn-based games available for mobile, period.

Heavy on the detail and strategy, this game is perfect for someone looking to manage a complicated enterprise. Bonus, the developers are constantly updating and improving the game for free. In app purchases are few far between and not necessary. Love it, can't wait for more. 10/10

content: I love this game but miss the market trading (and combat) of Star Traders, if only this game could incorporate those elements

Best in class 4X style game for the Android platform. Addictive, atmospheric gameplay slightly let down by unclear statistics. The game balance is superb. The warship design editor and faction diplomacy are both novel ideas and are very compelling. Kept me going for about 2 months and regular updates often pull me back for another go.

So far I think this game is well put together. It has a good atmosphere plus very strategic gameplay elements. You have to take some time and go through the help list to fully grasp and understand how it functions but once you do it traps you in but in a good way. Take the tutorial first and go through the help menu because if you don't you could easily become lost in this game. If you like hardcore strategic games give it a shot and if your wondering if it will be to overbearing, try it out free free first

If you're looking for a good 4x look no further,  because, holy crap, the Trese Bros. have knocked it out if the park with this game. Star Traders 4x isn't a clone of any previous 4x, it's a unique take on the genre that sees you playing against your own empire as you try to keep the squabbling factions under your care from being invaded by an alien menace. I implore you to try to lite version if you like 4x games even remotely.

I love the whole controlling three separate factions that have some freedom on how they interact with each other. However the game mechanics for ships being completely different from the rpg has really thrown my sense of whether or not a ship is good.

The biggest problem is the lack of an Options screen. Also, I purchased all the unlocks in the free version, but the full version still has them locked. I payed $14 when I expected to pay $9, and I don't want to pay an extra $4. At least add a data transfer option like your other games.
replyContent: Please e-mail me if you are having problems with getting your IAP and Purchases to work. You can reach me at cory.trese@gmail.com I am here 24/7 to support any issues with purchases, refunds or the IAP. I will make sure Google resolves the issue with the payments promptly. I will look forward to your e-mail.

content: Great game!

It became a 30 minute survive and get colony ships in the air and restart from scratch that failed the aliens had a lot of friends so I was destroyed but I enjoyed every second so I bought the game and round 2 began.
It,s awsomw

Loving it

Just one more turn and I'll put it down...

replyContent: @jatarra - if you've go the Elite app installed, you have access to the 6 original Factions, including 3 Great Houses - Javat, Thulun, and Steel Song.  The expansion 3 Great Clans, Alta Mesa, Moklumne, and Zenrin require the Great Clans IAP.

content: Must-have for 4X TBS enthusiasts. A complex research and economic system in the game. I like customising my ships, however the models are greatly limited and I would love a ship model editor where you drag and drop parts :)

Great game

replyContent: @ian - the tutorial mission has semi-slow and weak AI and is setup to allow you to get a grasp of the system and then win.  Try some of the other maps, add more enemies, and increase the difficulty level.  Once you win, the aliens will not return, but you can play on to explore the game more if you want.

content: The only games I actually get excited about updating are by the Trese Brothers... Your not just getting fixes but what seems to be a never ending stream of universe enhancing, highly detailed, free expansions... Highly recommend all their work, they've got something for everyone... üòä

Too clunky and progresses like molasses without AI Management

I just want to say I recently bought Civilization Revolutions, & despite all the fancy eye candy, Star Traders 4x beats it hands down! The best 4x currently on the play store, I've had this game for months & it's only getting better! The only 4x that will beat this is a sequel.
Even if I slowly lose because of overpopulation and not enough cash to maintain my fleets, the game is still epic as all hell! I love it!

I just dove in the game and had fun learning what to do next and how

Epic 4x for android. The extensive ship design is my favourite aspect. Like all TB games, you will not be disappointed with this one.
Long time player of ST and sure to be on this one too! Great job guys!!
Exactly what I was looking for. Great game.
Space strategy game worthy of your time.
You make the best games and come up with your own ideas and don't just go for what's trending which normally suck duck nipples your my heroes hopefully some day I can code like you ;)

This is a very good turn based strategy game, probably the best on mobile devices. You have to manage your own factions with diplomacy, balance your economy, and fend off the enemy at the same time. A bit daunting at first, once you get the hang of it... Qaulity devs, frequent updates and a good community website make this a must own game.

You can tell from the quality of the game, mechanics and UI that the devs really care. The non-consumable, not pay to win IAP policy makes it an easy buy. Devs listen to players, and updates are regular. Tons of new content added for free since I started playing. Great Game!
Love this game
A worthy worthy successor to moo and moo2 with ton new and challenging mechanics. Don't just take my word for it, try it out the free version first, then buy it
Awesome! Civ-like game with really in-depth ship customization. Great devs!

The Trese Brothers have a powerful, engaging, and well built 4X game which includes regular updates, fixes, and friendly support. An amazing small development team!

OK, this game does not measure up to MOO, GalCiv, or Civilization.   But the availability of a reasonably engaging mobile 4X game is a minor miracle. And the constant updating by the Trese brothers can't be commended enough.

Amazing depth. I've always dreamed of a good 4X I could carry in my pocket. Visit the forums and interact with the community and the developers, if you have any good ideas they may even use them. Awesome game from awesome developers! Edit: keeps getting better with constant updates expanding technology tree and new ships to.play with.
This 4X is not a civ clone it has a unique and challenging political system unlike any other strategy game I have played. Love it!

A supplement to the original star traders game by the brothers.  Help it in steam too. Check the posts above or search it out  on steam
This game is friggin awesome. I love it. Well worth the $5! Only thing I have a problem with is there is no tutorial. So I have no idea what I am doing lol.

replyContent: @ben - thanks for the feedback.  We have recently fixed the bug where you could buy treaties you could not afford for 0 Credits.  If you'd like to chat more about the game's economy or report other bugs, don't hesitate to email me at atrese@gmail.com

content: Great fun! Good depth of play! Excellent RPG!
Awesome game

Yet another great game from these two. This one takes a little more patience but is terribly fun if you line a long empire builder. Only thing wrong with it is that it distracts me from my cyber knight and templar assault teams...

Great. Once the gameplay is worked out its terrific

I bought this game nearly immediately when it came out, to support an ambitious 4x on Android. Unfortunately after having some more planets, it got rather tedious due to all the micromanaging involved to manage your planets (and the buildings on it). Other games give you governors/ai that can be configured and finetuned to do this job automatically for you. I really hope they will add something like this too. If it weren't for this point the game would be definitely great. I stopped playing very soon though..
replyContent: I'm working on an auto-building AI that you can use if you don't complete control over the empire's construction agenda. Some players prefer to focus on the tactics and ship design elements of the game, and I respect that. I need time to get the AI right or it will generate more low ratings than it removes. E-mail cory.trese@gmail if I can help

content: These guys have a monoply on the games I play on my phone. Great game, highly recommend!

As with all trese brothers games, this is a prime example of quality indie game development, no greedy IAPs, simple straightforward learning curve and highly in depth end game, an instapurchase well invested.

This is a fun, polished 4x strategy game on Android. The only thing that needs to be added is multiplayer. The devs are some of the best devs on Android, and they listen to their fans, so it will probably be added later.
Best 4X game I've found. I go to bed passing it, and I can't wait to take up and get another hour in. A feature that would be cool would be to sync games between devices.
If you are a fan of 4x TBS's then this is just the mobile game for you!

Had taken a break from the Trese Bros games to up my productivity and have more family time. Got this when first released but kept putting off playing it. Got excited talking about the TBs and their games a couple days ago and decided to play ST4X. Running on 6 hours sleep in last 3 days and can't stop...the Xeno are massing and I'm building the fleet to repel them and seize their worlds. It's another smash hit from the brothers and now I'm doomed to spend all my available free time back in their world. Who needs a real life and family anyways we've got the Trese brothers and their sock puppets. :)
It took me a bit of time to get acclimated but now this game invades my dreams. I'm a fan of all Trese Bros games. This deepens my appreciation for the others. Challenging and endlessly replayable.

Spending lots of time with this game. It does so many things right and does justice to the 4x platform. Regular updates and additions from this developer. Best on a tablet, but doable on a phone with zoom. I excpect to spend lots more time with this game. My only complaint is that save games do not span devices. If there were a way for games to sync across devices that would be awesome. I would also like to see a random map generator added at some point. Minor things that are a personal preference though.
replyContent: @corey - we have provided this walkthrough for backup / restore / transferring saved games between devices.  It is not a cloud-save solution, and is not intended to be used to move games around constantly, but it may help, and is especially useful if changing phones - http://www.tresebrothers.com/transfer-saved-games-between-devices/

content: Wow! This game is great. The devs really are dedicated to improving this game and listening to feedback from players. Updates keep me running to Wi-Fi to see what's new. content: Great 4X game! There are so few games in that genre available on Android, and even fewer with that level of polish. The graphics are a step up from Star Traders but could have been better. All that said, core of the game is excellent and highly recommended.  :-)
replyContent: There is a technology called "Planetary Invasion" which gets you the "Military Transport" ship which can Invade an alien world. The Transport ship needs a "Drop Ship" weapon and the "Invasion" Training option. The video tutorial for this is still a work in progress. If you need support, e-mail cory.trese@gmail.com

content: Another epic game from the Trese Bros.

What I love about this game and the developers in general is that they are original in the literal sense of the word. They return to gaming origins and make essential tweaks to established formats. This game is complex where it needs to be, and simplifies less important areas. For instance, research leads to a complex set of choices that have varied effects on your empire, while trade agreements and political treatises are handled by a touch of a button. Also, your 4X competitor, the xenos, is a non-negotiable enemy, so that you know you have to build a fleet at some point in the game. You can design your own ships using the many reactors, weapons and training options that are all made available by your research tactics. This game is very addictive and fun to play. An essential purchase for any gamer.

Trese Bros., you guys have read my mind.  I've reeeally been craving some new, quality 4x action, and boom: this awesome game.  And it just keeps getting better due to frequent updates.  I own and love every game these guys have put out.  Their dedication to their work and customers is AMAZING.

Graphics look a bit 'fuzzy" on a 9" tablet screen -  probably look better on a smaller phone screen. Conversely buttons/text/info at bottom of that 9" screen look a bit small. But that's all just cosmetic. Seems a good game so far.

The game is a perfect example of how much content you can pack in a mobile game.   What's a little worrisome is that it can feel a little too much at times and that interface may not suited mobile devices, specifically cell phones.   I'd be interested to try this on a tablet or again on Steam when it arrives.   Definitely the best, if not only,  4X Strategy game on mobile and one of the better ones in all the genre.
But the economics need a lot of tweaking. This is one of those 4x games where your problem with population is that you have too much, not too little.
The Treese Brothers make some enjoyable games, and this is one of their best conceived games yet.
You like loosing hours playing a devilishly hard strategy game. Download
Keep up the good work. Wouldn't mind some extra movment for my support ships though...
replyContent: The computer AI does pay upkeep, some of the Alien AI pay almost 200% of the upkeep the player does, to slow them down. Extra movement for support ships might be something you could add with a customized Ship Design. If there is anything we can do to earn a 5* review, please e-mail me at my personal address cory.trese@gmail.com thanks for playing!
